<item>
            <title>[FLINK-1482] BlobStore does not delete directories when process is killed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-1482</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The BlobStore (BlobCache + BlobServer) does not delete the blob store directory if it is not properly shutdown. This happens if one kills the process as it is done by Flink&apos;s start and stop shell scripts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can solve the problem by registering a shutdown hook to do the cleanup. The shutdown hook has to delete a unique directory which has been created by the blob store.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
